http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/New-railway-line-inaugurated/article13991126.ece

The new railway double line between Harlapur, Somapur and Bannikoppa was opened for trains on Saturday.A release from the South Western Railway (SWR) stated that the line doubling works of this stretch was completed and the Commissioner of Railway Safety (CRS) granted authorisation for movement of trains after conducting inspection.The Rail Vikas Nigam Limited (RVNL) had taken up this work as part of Hosapete-Tanaighat railway line doubling works.As trains will now be moving on both the lines in this section, people are advised to be more careful while crossing the unmanned gates.